Birds.2 The scene is laid in a wild‚ uninhabited country, with

a bunch of shrubbery in the background. Enter two Athe- nians, Peithetaerus (Plausible) and Euelpides (Hopeful). They carry birds on their hands to guide them to a region where they will be free from the troubles of Athenian life.
